title: Handbook of Safeguarding Global Financial Stability: Political,
description:
English | ISBN: 0123978750 | 2013 | 754 pages | PDF | 7 MB 

Political and social forces exert pressure on our globalized economy in many forms, from formal and informal policies to financial theories and technical models. 

Our efforts to shape and direct these forces to preserve financial stability reveal much about the ways we perceive the financial economy.
